Tom,<br><br>
Thanks for sharing your thoughts and feelings about Monte Grappa. On our journey through the mountains to Volturino, my wife picked out several pillboxes and other obvious WW2 fortifications. We also passed a cemetery of WW2 Allied fallen, hundreds of tiny crosses in a field. <br><br>
I could not help feeling the connection to our brothers of WW2 as I passed the same way as they did so long ago. It was like a time warp. Although the landscape had healed, the feelings brought me back to Nam in some respects. <br><br>
Some things just never end, do they?<br><br>

